SIMPLE: fastness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fastness
<hw>Fast"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>f⟦ae⟧stnes</ets>, fr.
<ets>f⟦ae⟧st</ets> fast. See <er>Fast</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being fast and firm; firmness; fixedness;
security; faithfulness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All . . . places of <qex>fastness</qex> [are] laid open.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir J. Davies.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A fast place; a stronghold; a fortress or fort; a
secure retreat; a castle; <as>as, the enemy retired to their
<ex>fastnesses</ex> in the mountains</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Conciseness of style.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Ascham.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>The state of being fast or swift.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fastuous</ent>⟦br⟧
